news.title: Delhi HC quashes DDA demolition notice for encroachment removal in Mehrauli
news.para: A bench headed by Chief Justice Satish Chandra Sharma said regardless of the environmental imperatives or earlier court orders, the DDA's obligation to act as per law and ensure procedural fairness to those affected by its actions remains intact.

news.title: NBCC (India)'s net profit declines 16.19% in Q2 FY24
news.para: NBCC (India)'s net consolidated total income stood at Rs 2,129.09 crore in Q2 FY24, a growth of 2.66 per cent from Rs 2,073.89 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Orient Cement posts net profit of Rs 24.62 crore in Q2 FY24
news.para: Orient Cement's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 722.24 crore in Q2 FY24, a growth of 16.47 per cent from Rs 620.11 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Coimbatore corporation to resume installation of streetlights
news.para: During the recent council meeting, city mayor Kalpana Anand Kumar had assured that there would not be any compromise on the quality of the lights.

news.title: Shalimar Paints' net loss widens to Rs 25.62 crore in Q2 FY24
news.para: Shalimar Paints' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 121.41 crore in Q2 FY24, a growth of 8.57 per cent from Rs 111.83 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Pimpri Chinchwad: PCMC gets cracking on dust pollution, to hold officials accountable for lapses
news.para: While a majority of these guidelines already exist, PCMC now aims at enforcing them strictly, for which dedicated squads have been deployed in each ward to ensure compliance.

news.title: Finolex Cables posts net profit of Rs 154.18 crore in Q2 FY24
news.para: Finolex Cables' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 1,229.27 crore in Q2 FY24, a growth of 10.09 per cent from Rs 1,116.61 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Delhi civic body to take punitive action against property tax defaulters
news.para: “Considering it is a major source of revenue, it has been decided to take strict action to recover property tax from defaulters,” said the circular.

news.title: Burnpur Cement posts net loss of Rs 19.11 crore in Q2 FY24
news.para: Burnpur Cement's net standalone total income stood at Rs 43.48 crore in Q2 FY24, a growth of 31.64 per cent from Rs 33.03 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Kolkata civic body to hike fee by 75% to clean vacant plots
news.para: ​The proposal was passed in the mayor-in-council meeting on Wednesday with the vector control department officials hoping the hike would ensure better compliance by owners in keeping their properties garbage-free.

news.title: Cidco extends deadline for housing scheme payments till January 10, 2024
news.para: ​​The defaulters will have to pay the entire amount of their respective tenements along with delayed payment charges by the new deadline. The extension has been granted based on the request of the applicants.

news.title: Kolkata: Builders must pay NOC fees to NKDA for modifications in building plan
news.para: ​​NKDA on Wednesday issued a notification in this regard. Officials said the decision was approved in the latest NKDA board meeting.

news.title: Sparkle Two Mall Developers buys land parcel in Thane for Rs 429 crore
news.para: Sparkle Two Mall Developers, a wholly-owned subsidiary of The Phoenix Mills, has paid an amount of Rs. 400.87 crore under two conveyance deeds.

news.title: Haryana bans construction as air gets dirtier
news.para: The state’s AQI has dipped slightly, yet the air quality remains severe in five districts, very poor in another eight, poor in five, and moderately poor in the rest, with Panchkula recording the lowest AQI of 128 points.

news.title: Greater Noida panel to resolve builder-buyer logjam now
news.para: The city, which is home to 191 residential complexes, sees frequent disputes between residents and representatives of builders or AOAs over matters like issuing NOCs or formation of apartment owners’ associations (AOAs), that reach the Authority.

news.title: Sebi streamlines process for investors to access unclaimed funds in REITs, InvITs, debt securities
news.para: The new framework will come into effect from March 1, 2024, the Securities and Exchange Board of India (Sebi) said in three separate circulars.

news.title: Noida DM asks builders to ramp up anti-pollution measures, warns of penalty
news.para: Gautam Buddh Nagar District Magistrate Manish Verma underlined that all construction works in the district is banned for the time being except for hospitals and the Noida International Airport in Jewar, according to an official statement.

news.title: Maharashtra government to acquire Air India building for Rs 1,601 crore
news.para: The 23-storey building is owned by Air India Assets Holding Limited, a company created by the union ministry of civil aviation in 2018 to manage all Air India-owned properties.

news.title: Kinnteisto LLP buys office spaces for Rs 739 crore in Mumbai's BKC and Andheri
news.para: Rekha Jhunjhunwala is the wife of late billionaire stockholder Rakesh Jhunjhunwala, who had earned the sobriquet of India’s Warren Buffett through his four-decade investing career in Mumbai.

news.title: The Phoenix Mills' net profit grows 36.92% in Q2 FY24
news.para: The Phoenix Mills' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 906.64 crore in Q2 FY24, a growth of 32.65 per cent from Rs 683.49 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.
